This paper discusses a new field-normalized bibliometric indicator, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The paper focuses on the evaluation of research publications, which is a common topic in digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves analyzing citation patterns, which is relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of research publications, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
